<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 5:47PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of south central
Cascade County through 630 PM MDT...
At 546 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles southeast of Cascade, moving north at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Heavy rain, winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of south central
Cascade County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
